---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Blog — Aivyx" description="Articles about privacy-first AI, encryption, multi-agent systems, and building with Aivyx.">
  <section class="page-hero">
    <h1>Blog</h1>
    <p>Deep dives into privacy, encryption, agent architecture, and building with Aivyx.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="blog-grid">
    <article class="blog-card featured">
      <div class="card-tag">Launch</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/why-i-built-a-privacy-first-ai-agent" target="_blank">Why I Built a Privacy-First AI Agent</a></h2>
      <p>Every AI tool sends your data to the cloud. I built one that doesn't. The story behind Aivyx and why privacy-first AI matters.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Security</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/chacha20-hmac-chains" target="_blank">ChaCha20 + HMAC Chains: Encrypting AI Memory</a></h2>
      <p>A technical deep dive into Aivyx's encryption architecture — key derivation, authenticated encryption, and tamper-proof audit chains.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>10 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Tools</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/mcp-tools" target="_blank">46 Tools and Infinite Extensibility: MCP in Aivyx</a></h2>
      <p>How Aivyx combines built-in tools with Model Context Protocol for infinite extensibility.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Architecture</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/the-nonagon" target="_blank">The Nonagon: How 9 AI Agents Collaborate</a></h2>
      <p>Inside Aivyx's multi-agent team system — nine specialists working together on complex missions.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Compliance</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/audit-logs" target="_blank">Tamper-Proof Audit Logs for AI Agents</a></h2>
      <p>Why your AI agent needs accountability and how HMAC chains create a verifiable record of every action.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Voice</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/voice-agent" target="_blank">Building a Voice AI Agent in Rust</a></h2>
      <p>Real-time voice interaction with STT/TTS, barge-in interruption, and full tool access during voice sessions.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Architecture</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/dag-orchestration" target="_blank">DAG-Based Task Orchestration</a></h2>
      <p>How Aivyx decomposes complex tasks into dependency graphs and executes them in parallel with reflection loops.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Protocols</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/a2a-mcp" target="_blank">A2A + MCP: Two Protocols, One Agent Platform</a></h2>
      <p>How Aivyx implements both MCP (agent-to-tool) and A2A (agent-to-agent) for complete interoperability.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Self-Host</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/ollama" target="_blank">Local AI with Ollama: No Cloud Required</a></h2>
      <p>How to set up a fully private AI agent using Aivyx and Ollama — zero data leaves your machine.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>9 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Skills</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/skills" target="_blank">22 Skills That Turn Your AI Agent Into a Professional</a></h2>
      <p>How structured skills produce expert-level output — from code review to security audit.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Distributed</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/federation" target="_blank">Agent Federation: Distributed AI Across Instances</a></h2>
      <p>How Aivyx agents on different servers collaborate with Ed25519 trust verification and federated memory.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="blog-card">
      <div class="card-tag">Interfaces</div>
      <h2><a href="https://dev.to/aivyx/interfaces" target="_blank">From TUI to Desktop: Three Ways to Use Aivyx</a></h2>
      <p>CLI for scripts, TUI for power users, Desktop for setup — a guide to Aivyx's three interfaces.</p>
      <div class="card-meta">
        <span>March 2026</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>8 min read</span>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 4rem 2rem 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .page-hero p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .blog-grid {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 4rem;
    padding: 0 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .blog-card {
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
    transition: border-color 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .blog-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .blog-card.featured {
    border-color: var(--accent);
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(232,168,73,0.08), transparent);
  }

  .card-tag {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    background: rgba(232,168,73,0.12);
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .blog-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .blog-card h2 a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .blog-card h2 a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .blog-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .card-meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .blog-card { padding: 1.25rem; }
    .blog-card h2 { font-size: 1.05rem; }
  }
</style>
